Armor Class
Armor Class - Last Edited: 2007-04-20 14:02:09 by Unknown
=========================================================
Armor Class - AC
Armor Class is a rating of how tough you are against physical attacks. The more armor you wear, the better protected you are. Typically, the heavier the armor, the better the protection. However, enchanted armor can provide you with more protection as well as have less of an encumbrance.
Base AC is around 0 and granting 0% damage reduction, if you are naked, and have normal agility. Equipment that affects your AC by -values will reduce the damage you take in melee combat (i.e. a robe that grants -10 AC will reduce the damage you receive by 1%). -1000 AC would result in 100% melee damage reduction if such a feat were possible, but is not.
AC property on items is physical protection granted by them and is strictly related to the material item is made of. As you may expect materials like cloth, feathers, bark grant very little or next to none physical protection while rare metals like mithril or adamantium make extremely durable armors. The total bonus granted by the item also depends on the location it is designed for. Body armors are more important than masks or bracelets. Also full body armors are considerably more effective than set of separate chestplate, sleeves and leggings of the same material.
Armor, spiritarmor|Spirit Armor, phantomarmor|Phantom Armor, vaporarmor|Vapor Armor, enhancearmor|Enhance Armor, Barkskin, Baladorsprotection|Baladors Protection, and songofprotection|Song of Protection grant bonuses to armor class; whereas, coldsnap|Cold Snap, Blindness, faeriefire|Faerie Fire, and Wither will weaken armor class.
