Chanting is a talent developed by monks used to further enhance their
martial arts skills. There are a number of different chants available to
monks, all varying in power and purpose.
*     Heroism - Heroism elevates the amount of adrenaline produced by the chanter
and stimulates the centers of the mind controlling dexterity and balance,
resulting in increased combat abilities. For the follower of the 'Way of
the Snake' this rush of adrenaline also increases speed and movement while
the Dragon Disciples become immune to fear.
*     Calm - Calm soothes whoever or whatever might be angry at the chanter or
his friends. This chant has the capability of ceasing combat in certain
situations.
*     Quivering Palm - This chant causes the chanter's hand to vibrate so fast it
can barely be seen. The hand then strikes out at equally fast speeds,
inflicting formidable damage upon its target.
*     Regenerate - When chanting Regenerate, the monk heals at a much faster
rate.
*     Buddha Palm - Buddha Palm, much like Quivering Palm, causes the monk's
hands to vibrate at unbelievable speeds. However, the Buddha Palm strikes
out with both hands at lightning speed at as many adversaries as it can.
*     Chi Purge - This ability allows the monk to focus his or her chi, curing
their body of the more detrimental maladies in the realm of Duris. What affects
it is capable of curing, however, is greatly dependent on the skill in this area
and the level of the monk.
