Cramped
Cramped - Last Edited: 2007-04-22 22:12:53 by Unknown
=====================================================
A cramped room is a very tiny pathway with only 2 exits.
When entering a cramped room, all players and mobs are forced into a single file line, and may only cast spells and engage those who are next to them.  Additionally, only those near the exits may leave the room normally.  All others will bump into those who are standing in the room.
To get through a cramped room, one should recline.  Moving while in such position results in a squirming action, which while is not always effective, can get through the cramped room.  It is much too difficult to squirm past those who are fighting in a cramped room.
Area spells and transportation spells are also unusable in cramped rooms.
While mounted, one cannot fit through these tiny pathways.
