Enchant
Enchant - Last Edited: 2008-11-24 15:16:20 by Blaize
====================================================
This skill will imbue a piece of equipment of your choosing with any spell
up to a certain power that is currently affecting the casting player.
There are some restrictions in the type of spells that may be enchanted.
- Artifacts cannot be enchanted.
- Offensive spells or any spells that are of the "self only" cast type cannot
be enchanted into the item.
- Only one enchant affect can be held on a piece of equipment at any one time
and the effect will wear off in the appropriate time span.
Enchanting an item can be an expensive exercise and you will need to carry
the necessary funds to use this skill. An enchanted item will display a flag
indicating that status if successful, however, beware that unsuccessful
enchant attempts may permanently damage the item in the process.
Example Syntax: enchant cloak 'vitality'
The knowledge of this ability is imparted by a Dwarven Smith within a Tribal
Oasis.
NOTE: Choosing to learn this epic skill will prevent the player from pursuing
any knowledge in the Spellbind epic skill.
