Exp
Experience - Last Edited: 2016-03-05 00:16:57 by gellz
======================================================
Syntax:   exp (to see how much experience you currently have)
Whenever you kill a monster or a player, you earn experience points. Once
you have earned enough experience, you raise a level in your class. Duris
has 56 mortal levels, 56 for multiclasses as well; you can check your progress
by typing "experience". The levels after 46 are only received by gaining epic
points. After level 50, receiving epics from a zone specified for your next level
is required to attain that next level, provided you have the necessary experience
and have earned the total amount of required epic points.
Here are a few things you should know about experience points:
-Humans and Orcs gain an experience bonus, which might make them desirable classes for newer players.  This also comes in handy when multiclassing (see: Help multiclass), as these characters are required to level twice.
-Each pulse you hit or miss a monster when you are engaged you get experience points.
-Healing a person who is in combat and grouped with you will give you a lot of experience points.
-You get exp for each spell you cast upon a monster or a player in your group if you are in combat.
The amount of experience points received depends on which circle the spells is in.
You also receive experience points for using skills in combat, such as bash, backstab, kick and so on.
-If you kill a monster of a higher level than yourself, you get bonus experience points.
-If you kill a monster of a lower level, you will gain less experience points.
-Rested and well rested bonuses (bonuses obtained after staying offline for a certain amount of time) will apply a higher level of exp temporarily.  (See Rested for details)
The amount of experience you receive depends on the type of monster you kill as well.
See help mobs for more information.
==See also==
group, trophy, death, epic, mobs, blood
