Frag
Frag - Last Edited: 2008-04-14 15:58:43 by Blaize
=================================================
Syntax:     frag
            frag <classname>
            frag <racename>
            frag <racewarsidename>
The term "frag", originally taken from the Vietnam War, is when you kill
another player. When you kill someone who is an opposite racewar side
(a Human killing a Drow, etc) you get a frag if you are within 10 levels
of them. When you are killed by someone who is an opposite racewar side
(a Gnome being killed by a Ogre, ect) you lose a frag if within 10 levels
of them. All frags are split between the group equally accounting for all
the players of that side in the room. So, if you are with a group of five
people and you kill one player, you will each receive .20 frags. Likewise,
if you are alone and four others are in the room when you kill one player,
you alone will receive .20 frags. Typing "fraglist" will show a list of
the top ten and lowest ten fraggers in the mud. Or, you may type "frag
<racewarside>", "frag <classname>" or "<frag racename>".
Once a player has more than 20 frags, he or she will not gain frags for
slaying anyone under level 40.
