Godparticipation
Godparticipation - Last Edited: 2007-04-22 22:12:53 by Unknown
==============================================================
This refers to the level to participation each god is expected to
contribute to the MUD. In order to obtain and maintain a god of some power
here on Duris, each god is expected to continually contribute in some
fashion.
The point the Forgers are trying to make is that it is a *privilege* to be
a god here on Duris, not a right. Once you have earned your immortality,
you are an example to all others below you, mortal or immortal, and there
will always be others that, given the chance, would gladly take your
position.
You are expected to contribute to the MUD in some fashion and on a regular
basis. Unlike some MUDs, you cannot create one or two zones, earn a god,
and ride on fame forever. We do NOT, however, mean that you have to work
every day (or even every month), but *some* type of contribution from every
god is necessary to keep Duris expanding and growing.
All gods will be assessed on a regular basis and assessments will be
handled in this manner:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Each month, during the Forgers" regular meeting, each god (including
