Guild
Guild - Last Edited: 2013-05-07 21:03:09 by drannak
===================================================
A guild is a group of players who have banded together for mutual
communication and support.
==How To Begin A Guild==
The requirements for forming an guild are as follows:
 * All members must be at least 25th level or above.
   The level requirement is simply to ensure that members
   are familiar with Duris and how it's run.
 * Guilds must keep a member count of at least 3 members.
 * Guild names MUST be reasonably thematic and not overly silly or
offensive.
 * It costs 5000 platinum to form a new guild.
To form a guild, find your racewar's guild leader and list:
Goodies - Tharnadia, 1n, 1w from the crier.
Evils   - Khildarak, 2s, 1w from the inn.
==Leaders==
Once the guild is created, the player forming the guild will be
flagged as a guild 'leader'. This will allow them to recruit members
into the guild and promote/demote them accordingly. This is done
completely by the leader and controlled by the code. Any new members will be
automatically be flagged and titled as a member of the guild. This also
will create a guild bank account which is accessible by Leaders and
Deputies.
Once a guild has been started and approved by a god, the guild
members of that guild must run their own activities. How many people
there are of a certain guild rank is entirely up to the players. The gods
themselves will have no interference with the running of the guild
themselves.
==Guild Structure==
Guilds have specific ranks within them which give their members to ability
do different things depending on their rank. How this works is as follows :
Leader -A leader can change the names of all the ranks (this allows an
guild of sorcerers to name the leader as "ArchMage" rather than "Leader".
These titles must be realistic in a fantasy world. A leader also has the
ability to flag a player as an enemy to the guild (leaders are the only
ones that can remove this flag as well). The leader can also add on an
'on parole' flag to members.
Deputy -A deputy (or higher) can delete, promote and demote members and
also has access to withdraw money from the guild's bank account.
Officer -An officer (or higher) has the right to fine lower members
(dealing out punishments etc).
Senior member -A senior member (or higher) has the right to enroll new
members.
Normal member -A Normal member just has general abilities, They can also see
what other guild members are online.
Enemy -The guild leader has the ability to flag a member as an
guild enemy as well. This will cause the guild npc's (if any)
to attack the player on sight and is used for betrayal etc.
Applying for Membership
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
In order to be allowed into a guild the player must first apply
himself as an applicant. You can do this by using the 'society apply
<player>' command where <player> is the enrolling member of the guild
you wish to join.
==Managing an Assocation==
* Manage members/policy with the 'society' command.
==See also==
Society, Society Examples
