Hitpoints
Hitpoints - Last Edited: 2007-04-22 22:12:53 by Unknown
=======================================================
Hitpoints, or hp, or h/H in the prompt, are vital to any player of Duris because
it is the amount of life you have. Damage will reduce this amount of life and if
you happen to drop below -2 hitpoints you will slowly bleed to death if someone
doesn't finish you off or bandage/heal you. Hitpoints regenerate slowly, though
they faster when reclining and asleep; also, there are heal rooms and certain
spells can aid in the regeneration process.  Equipment to raise your hitpoints
is available, but there is a limit to how much it will affect you.  Larger races
tend to have higher hitpoints than smaller races due to their racial constition,
the attribute responsible for determining the amount of hitpoints you have.
Equipment that affects your constitution and CON_MAX will raise your hitpoints,
and thus the cap on how much hp equipment you can wear.
