Magic User
Magic User - Last Edited: 2007-04-20 14:02:09 by Unknown
========================================================
The term "Magic-User" defines a class of individuals who spend their lives
training in the use of arcane magical spellcraft. They are the ones who
stand at the back of a party during battle and hurl powerful offensive
spells at the enemy. Because they are so powerful in their discipline, they
are typically the most frail in stature.
There are subclasses of Magic-User, each with their own specialties:
Sorcerer, Necromancer, Illusionist and Conjurer. Being part of the larger class-group, these classes are affected by the same class restrictions on equipment and are similar in
to-hit rolls and average hit points. There are also some other classes that
only loosely fall within the "Magic-User" definition, these are:
Psionicist and Alchemist. These sub-classes tend to have similar
resistances and susceptibilities to things like spells, paralysis, dragon
breath, etc. Each sub-class rises in level according to its own experience
chart.
