Mobs - Last Edited: 2009-08-17 06:07:58 by Kharne
=================================================
The term mob or mobs refers to NPC's on duris.  Mobs can be any race,
class and level. Mobs add variety to the zones and maps of Duris.
These modifiers take effect for mobs level 20 and higher (not your
level, the mob's level).
From worst to best...
(Massive exp penalty)Mobs with no memory (Massive exp penalty)
(exp penalty)Animals (including but not limited to carnivores,
    spiders, worms, etc...)(exp penalty)
(Exp penalty)Pure Warrior / hitters mobs
(Small to no exp penalty) Hybrid hitter mobs
    (including but not limited to mercenaries, rogues, and avengers)
(Exp bonus)Mobs that track players that run from them(Exp bonus)
(Exp bonus)Giants, elementals, undead, and other tougher races(Exp bonus)
(Exp bonus)Casters (including but not limited to sorcerers, conjurers, etc...)(Exp bonus)
(Massive exp bonus)Greater races and elite mobs (including but not
    limited to demons, dragons, angels,
    beholders...) (Absolute best exps)(Massive exp bonus)
Examples:
Colorless worms (animal + no memory) are horrible exp, basically nothing.
Human warriors are poor exps.
Giant warriors are decent exps.
Human sorcerers are very nice exps.
Giant sorcerers are awesome exps.
Demon sorcerers are insane exps.
The meanest and deadliest mobs are worth vasts amounts of exps...
The little insignificant mobs that you can wade through with one hand
  tied behind your back are worth basically nothing.
