Multi-user dungeon
Multi-user dungeon - Last Edited: 2007-04-22 22:12:53 by Unknown
================================================================
In computer gaming, a MUD (Multi-User Dungeon or Domain or Dimension) is a multi-player computer game that combines elements of role-playing games, hack and slash style computer games and social interaction. Typically running on an internet server, the game is usually text driven, where players read descriptions of rooms, objects, events, other characters, and computer-controlled creatures (Mobs)or non-player characters (NPCs) in a virtual world. Players usually interact with each other and the surroundings by typing commands that resemble a natural language, usually English. MUDs are typically fashioned around the dice rolling rules of the Dungeons & Dragons (D&D) series of games.
Duris MUD implements a fantasy world populated by good and evil races with players being able to take on any number of classes in order to gain specific skills or abilities. The object of the game is to gain experience, explore a rich fantasy world, complete quests, and fight in the world-wide racewars.
