Naval Guide - Last Edited: 2007-04-22 22:12:53 by Unknown
=========================================================
Ship Code is another great aspect of the Duris world. It creates the oppurtunity to make great money by sailing cargo around the world and selling products at port to generate personal or guild wealth. It can also be dangerous as enemy gunships may be patrolling looking to cut off your monetary supply and send your ship to the bottom of the ocean. They may also set up naval blockades to prevent you from attacking their guild who may be doing a quest in some of the island areas of Duris.
Here is a basic guide to start you on your way to becoming a mariner in the world of Duris.
Buying Your Ship
If you have the platinum coins and are looking to begin your adventures on the high seas, first go to one of the many dock areas that can be found in Tharn, Good Continent Docks (just north of Tharnadia), Evermeet Docks, Myrabolus, Torrhan, Menden, Jade, Evil Continent Docks, Dalvik sells ships on KK, Stormport and Sarmiz. Walk to the resident shipbuilder and type list. The shipwright will then list the ships available for purchase. The ships generally available are:
Sloop (Baseline ship, room for one person only, high speed, low hitpoints and no room for cargo.)
Yacht (Room for two players, high speed, low hitpoints and an extremely small amount of room for cargo.)
Clipper (Room for 11 players, high speed, low/moderate hitpoints and a small amount of room for cargo.)
Frigate (Room for 13 players, moderate speed, moderate hitpoints and a moderate amount of room for cargo.)
Destroyer (Room for 15 players, moderate speed, moderate hitpoints and a moderate/high amount of room for cargo.)
Galleon (Room for 18 players, slow speed, high hitpoints and a high amount of room for cargo.)
Dreadnaught (Room for 25 players, slow speed, high hitpoints and large amount of room for cargo.)
