Parry
Parry - Last Edited: 2013-04-17 21:37:26 by targ
================================================
*Reflexive Skill
This skill is very similar to the dodge skill, but the one performing the
parry deflects the person's incoming attack rather than avoiding it. This is
the first step to performing a riposte.
A successful parry is based on many different factors. Dexterity is an
important variable and racial dexterity is used. What you see when viewing
attributes does not include racial bonuses or penalties.
Among other things, it is harder to parry if you are not standing, under the
influence of gaze, dazzled, blind, fighting a very strong opponent, or stunned.
It is impossible to parry an incoming attack from a whip or flail, and it is
impossible to parry with a whip or flail.
It is harder to parry an attacker's incoming blow if you are focused on
attacking something else.
It is also significantly harder to parry an attack when the attacker's strength
is much greater than your own.
Elite mobiles excel at parrying as do the blademaster and swashbuckler
classes.
==See also==
Agility, Dodge, Riposte, Strength
