Pop
Pop - Last Edited: 2007-04-22 22:12:53 by Unknown
=================================================
''Pop'' is a term used to describe when a zone has been reloaded.
Zones either ''pop'' on a regular timer or require the zone to be devoid of any players for a certain amount of time. There are even a few zones that only pop after a reboot, and will never ''repop'' throughout the duration of the boot.
During zone groups, the word ''pop'' is not one generally used to describe a favorable situation. During the event of a massrip, zones may pop, leaving corpses trapped deep within a zone. A sitter is an invaluable tool in keeping a zone from popping after a massrip.
During exp groups, once all the mobs have been slain, the group leader will usually lead everyone outside the zone, or move to another zone to continue the exp process until the previous zone has ''popped'', at which point the group will return, until all the mobs are once again dead.
See also: sitter, reboot, exp, mob
