Practice
Practice - Last Edited: 2008-03-14 19:13:12 by Blaize
=====================================================
This is the means to learn new spells or pay a teacher mob to
increase your skill proficiency
Spells:
Syntax: practice (to see a list of spells that may be scribed)
practice <spell> (while holding both a spellbook and quill
and resting)
practice all (this will scribe all spells into the book
currently held by the player if there is enough room left)
Practice is a method of scribing your spells. This is done with
the help of a teacher in the room. For this to be done, you must
have a spellbook and quill in hand and resting comfortably. You
can then "practice <spell>" to add a spell to your spellbook. If
this command is typed without any parameters and you are in the
presence of a teacher it will show your list of spells.
Skills:
Practicing skills can be done by either two options. The first
is passively "notching" skills by using them in or out of battle.
For instance a rogue may wish to practice 'hide' by attempting
to hide over and over. A second way to "notch" skills is by
finding the teacher mobs on the continent maps or in a Hometown,
and practicing skills at them by spending money.
Note: Skills will notch automatically to 40 as you gain levels.
