Pray
Pray - Last Edited: 2008-03-02 20:30:33 by Blaize
=================================================
Pray is the command used by certain classes to assign spell slots.  Using the pray command
without argument (simply typing pray) will list the spells prayed for and being prayed for
by the priest and will continue the process of praying for them if the priest is in the
proper position.  To pray for spells, the priest must be sitting, resting, and not in
combat.
Unlike scribing, praying does not require the priest to have spellbooks.  To "unpray" for
a spell use the forget command (using forget without argument will clear the praying
queue).
