Ranks
Ranks - Last Edited: 2008-03-17 15:39:17 by Blaize
==================================================
NOTE:  Ranks are currently disabled.
There are two group ranks: front and back.
==Rank Numbers==
At all times, more people will be in the front rank of your group than
in the back rank. The code enforces this for the most part, though there
are times (especially when someone dies or leaves the room) when it won't
immediately be updated.
==Rank Changes==
If you are in the rear rank, leave the room, and come back in, as with a
flee/return combo, you are automatically ranked to the front. Once you kill
one of the front ranked people, one of the rear ranked guys moves forward
(assuming equal numbers in front and back).
==Targeted spells==
Targeted spells can be targeted by anyone on anyone, regardless of which
group rank the caster and target are in.
==Area spells==
Area spells hit ALL ranks in front of you. This means if you are grouped
to the back rank, you will hit your front rank as well as both enemy ranks.
If you are ranked front, you will hit only the enemy group.
==Back Ranked==
People in the rear ranks are much harder to target with physical attacks.
They can be reached via Reach Weapons|reach weapons.
==General Theory==
Clearly a basic group format will have tanks and hitters in the front ranks,
with clerics and other casters in the rear ranks. However, experimentation
with various group formats is critical to success. There is not a single,
one size fits all solution that guarantees a win, you have to be flexible
and above all, you have to use your brain, especially with who the primary
targets will be for both casters as well as hitters.
NOTE:  Ranks are currently disabled.
