Ship looks
Ship looks - Last Edited: 2010-10-05 15:24:39 by kitsero
========================================================
Ship Looks
=========================================
==Look Out==
This command looks outside your ship, at the immediate surroundings. If
you are in a dock zone, it will tell you the available exits much like when
you are walking around normally. This will tell you other ships in your
square, and it will show you a small portion of the worldmap (in squares)
when you are outside.
==Look Tactical==
look tactical (optional parameters are <X> <Y>)
This will show you a tactical map centered on you (or x,y with 50,50
being the center of the map -ie YOU). It is displayed as a hex grid and
any nearby ships will be displayed according to their ID. The Hex grid is
the square setup basically "converted" to a hex grid, so it is not always
perfect in appearance. If the optional parameters <X> and <Y> are given the
map will center on that coord if it is within 35 hexes. This is a
calculated value, if you provide numbers outside the range, you will see an
error message. You cannot Look Tactical inside a dock zone.
==Look cargo==
This will tell you what cargo you currently have on your ship, and the
price you paid for that cargo.
==Look Status/Look Ship==
This will show you a detailed status of your ship with the state of your hull, armor and sails,
weapon status (whether its damaged, reloading or ready to fire) and ammo remaining.
It will also show your speed, heading and target. The ID number on
the upper right corner of the status display is your own current ID.
==Look Weaponspec==
This will show you the specifications of all your weapons. It will show
their weapon ranges and damage each shot will do as well as if the weapon
is destroyed or not.
==Look Sight <weapon number>==
If your have a target this command will show you your percentage to hit
the current locked target with that particular weapon.
==Look Contacts==
This will display a list of all ships within a scan range of your ship.
This is the heart of getting info on your target. The list is broken
into several parts and will look kinda like this:
Contact listing
[AN] "NorgDog"         X:53  Y:50  R:3.0   B:90  H:0   S:0 |SP
"AN" is the ship"s ID this is the parameter you pass to lock to lock onto
this target.
"Norgdog" is the ship"s name.
X:53 and Y:50 are their coords on your tactical map, so if you do a
"look tactical 53 50", it will center the map on Norgdog.
R:3.0 is Range, so in this case, Norgdog is 3 Squares from you.
B:90 is their bearing to you, so in this case, Norgdog is to your east
since 90 is east, so if you were to head east, you would be facing
Norgdog.
H:0 is Norgdog"s heading.. so in this case, Norgdog is facing north
since 0 is North.
S:0 is Norgdog"s speed so in this case, its not moving since it"s 0.
The first letter after separator (S), indicates it is on your starboard firing arc, so if you have
any weapons on your starboard side, they can fire at Norgdog.
The second letter (P) indicates, that Norgdog faces you with its port side, thus
you are likely to hit that side with your weapons (if their dispersion angle
is small).
There can be a third letter at the end of contact line:
blue   'F' - ship is floating in air
yellow 'A' - ship is anchored
red    'S' - ship is sinking
Note: White 'H:' and 'S:' on top of contact list show your own current heading and speed.
Note: when sailing, you should check your contacts as often as possible. This way you notice
any incoming danger early and can react in time.
